Name: Auditory Xanax
Description: I don’t want to hear a single thing that will prevent me from chilling and relaxing

Name: My coming of age anthem
Description: aka “My Anthem in college” aka “my early 20s anthem” aka “If Spotify wrapped existed 15 years ago, this would have been my no. 1 song”

Name: The dance floor is empty—you have one song to change that—GO
Cover better than the original—no boring answers
Description: No All Along the Watchtower by Hendrix, no Hurt by Johnny Cash, etc. Give us some non-obvious answers.

Name: Time Machine
Description: Music from the last 3 years that sounds completely retro/ from a different era

Name: Song with best build up and climax
Best long song
Description: anything over 6 minutes but please, keep it under an hour *cough* Dopesmoker

Name: Let’s get this party ended
Description:
Huge bummer songs that will make people leave the party

The song should be listenable and a real song. Not a novelty song or noise. Certainly not a 2 hour loop of fart noises (I won’t say if such a thing is available on Spotify)

It doesn’t have to be your favorite song or band, it should be a real viable actual song that you could imagine playing on the radio or a playlist, but the the lyrics or concept is such a fucking bummer that people can’t deal when they realize what’s going on.

Name: Artists with less than 300 monthly listeners on Spotify
Description: Let's try a variation on our final round tradition.
